  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is correct. An equation that defines a line in the <em>xy</em>-plane can be written as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals m x plus b\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"m\"><mi>m</mi></math> is the slope of the line and <mo></mo><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 0 comma b right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>)</mo></math><mo></mo> is its <em>y</em>-intercept. It&rsquo;s given that line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\"><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp;is defined by the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals 6 x plus 4\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math>; therefore, the slope of line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\"><mi>k</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6\"><mn>6</mn></math>.<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span>Since line<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span><em style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"j\"><mi>j</mi></math></em><span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span>is parallel to line<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span><em style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\"><mi>k</mi></math> </em>in the <em>xy</em>-plane&nbsp;and parallel lines have equal slopes, it follows that the slope of line<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"j\"><mi>j</mi></math></span> is<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6\"><mn>6</mn></math>. It&rsquo;s also given that line<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"j\"><mi>j</mi></math></span><span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span>passes through the point<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 0 comma 5 right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, which is its <em>y</em>-intercept.&nbsp;Substituting<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"6\"><mn>6</mn></math><span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span>for<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"m\"><mi>m</mi></math><span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span>and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5\"><mn>5</mn></math><span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span>for<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\"><mi>b</mi></math><span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span>in the equation<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals m x plus b\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math><span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span>yields<span style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"> </span><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y equals 6 x plus 5\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn></m